snippet.textDisplay:
Hey Rick!

Western PA golfer here, 9 handicap. First off, your content is outstanding. Really appreciate all you do.

I have had new drivers and I decided to change things up. I bought an almost new Titleist 905R, you know, the driver with the red arrows that everyone remembers. I tested it vs my newer clubs and put the same shaft in it ( Proforce V2 X) and I was really connecting. Longer and I liked how it felt heavier almost.

I'm curious if this was a club fitting anomaly (I cut my driver down 2" for comfort, control, and off the deck options) or if this club is on par with modern tech.

What are your thoughts? I doubt you'll see this comment but I would really appreciate your knowledge.

Best,
Oakes
snippet.textOriginal:

snippet.textDisplay: What is the point of doing an "on course" test with both drivers if you don't actually measure where each ball is going or even mark them separately and retrieve them? Instead you use a launch monitor that doesn't measure actual distance but rather uses an algorithm based on the launch data, i.e. your data will be identical whether the shot was hit on the course or into the net. Also, no mention of total distance. You can do better, Rick. Cheers.
